      },
      "63e14dd7-fdba-43cd-ae7d-51bbcedb6ebb/filter" : {
        "name" : "Only keep data if",
        "description" : "The filter is an expression that should return a boolean value that indicates whether a data item should be put into the corresponding output.Annotation values are available as variables. If an annotation has spaces special characters, use $ to access its value. Examples: <pre>#Dataset CONTAINS \"Raw\" AND condition EQUALS \"mock\"</pre><pre>TO_NUMBER($\"my column\") < 10</pre>\n\nThe expression result will be converted to a string. All existing annotations are available as variables that can be accessed directly, or if they contain special characters or spaces via the $ operator."
      },
