      },
      "2b9bdbee-b375-495e-8e73-26dd0f282a6b/file-path" : {
        "name" : "File path",
        "description" : "Expression that generates the output file path\n\nThis function should return a valid file path string, which can be either hardcoded or built using string or <code>PATH_COMBINE</code> operations.\n\nHard-cording file paths: Just type the path into quotes as shown below <pre>\"C:/MyData/Outputs/Output_file\"</pre>\n\nUsing path combination: You can combine combine variables provided from annotations and expression variables to, for example, save create a path relative to the project directory or to a project user path<pre>PATH_COMBINE(project_dir, \"Outputs\", \"Output_file\")</pre><pre>PATH_COMBINE(project_user_paths [\"outputs\"], \"Outputs\", \"Output_file\")</pre>Alternative: <pre>PATH_COMBINE(project_user_path.outputs, \"Outputs\", \"Output_file\")</pre>\n\nUsing expression functions: You can also use the standard string concatenation function to generate paths<pre>project_dir + \"/Outputs/Output_file\"</pre>"
      },
      "3e781fe1-fa24-4067-b81c-2a723fd636a5/jipipe:data-batch-generation/annotation-merge-strategy" : {
        "name" : "Merge same annotation values",
        "description" : "Determines which strategy is applied if data sets that define different values for the same annotation columns are encountered."
      },
      "2b9bdbee-b375-495e-8e73-26dd0f282a6b/jipipe:data-batch-generation/skip-incomplete" : {
        "pinned" : true,
        "name" : "Skip incomplete data sets",
        "description" : "If enabled, incomplete data sets are silently skipped. Otherwise an error is displayed if such a configuration is detected."
      },
      "e79737bd-0ea3-4cf3-a2a1-f1a4cd7b8e04/jipipe:adaptive-parameters/overridden-parameters" : {
        "important" : true,
        "name" : "Overridden parameters",
        "description" : "Here you can override the value of parameters based on annotations. The 'Value' settings should return a value for the parameter type or a JSON string that can be converted into a valid parameter value. The 'Parameter key' setting determines to which parameter this value is written to."
      },
      "54179c5e-ca57-444c-881b-c50ebe0ab98a/jipipe:node:description" : {
