      "05e784ad-ccb1-4f21-963f-9c19252344e3/label-data-annotation" : {
        "name" : "Label data annotation",
        "description" : "Determines which data annotation contains the labels. Please ensure that the appropriate label data is annotated to the raw input data.\n\nThis parameter is an expression that has two modes: (1) Selecting an existing annotation by its name, and (2) Matching an existing annotation by boolean operators<br/><ol><li>Type in the name of the existing annotation. Put the name in double quotes (optional, but recommended). Example: <pre>\"#Dataset\"</pre></li><li>The function iterates through all annotations. It should return TRUE for one of them. You will have 'key' and 'value' available within the expression. Example: <pre>key == \"#Dataset\"</pre></li></ol>"
      },
